attribute_information.business_name: The legal name the company has registered for itself with BC Registries.
attribute_information.business_type: The type of business as defined by the legislation governing BC Registries.
attribute_information.company_status: The status of the business at the time the credential is issued.
attribute_information.cra_business_number: A unique number assigned to the businessâ€™ BC Registries business program area by the Canada Revenue Agency (CRA).
attribute_information.credential_id: A unique identifier assigned by BC Registries that is specific to this person in their representation of this business.
attribute_information.family_name: The surname of the person representing the business, taken from the identity credential used to create the Registries Account for the individual.
attribute_information.given_names: The first and middle name(s), separated by spaces, of the person representing the business. Names are taken from the identity credential used to create the Registries Account for the individual.
attribute_information.identifier: A unique and permanent identifier that BC Registries creates and assigns to the business at the time the business is incorporated or registered with BC Registries.
attribute_information.registered_on_dateint: The date the business was incorporated or registered in BC with BC Registries.
attribute_information.role: The person's role(s) with the business, either determined by BC Registries (e.g., Incorporator) or as filed by the business with BC Registries (e.g., Director, Officer), that the business is required to report by legislation.
